  "title": "Artisanal Bread Baker / Culinary Chef",
  "description": "<p>To apply or find out more, please contact Leong Jia Wei (Reg No: R25157456) at WhatsApp +65 80358497<a href=\"http://wa.me/+6580358497\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"> </a>or email <a href=\"mailto:jiawei@placement.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">jiawei@placement.com.sg</a><br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Role Overview</strong></p><p>We’re looking for talented Artisanal Bread Bakers and Culinary Chefs for a local community artisan bakery in central Singapore, whose parent company also produces dried products like flour and malt.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Bake and deliver\n     high-quality handcrafted pastries</strong> using our rich natural ingredients and emphasizing deep flavour and texture</li><li>Monitor baking schedules to ensure a steady supply of fresh, visually stunning products.</li><li><strong>Follow food safety and hygiene guidelines</strong> (SFA\n     requirements, handwashing, glove use, proper storage).</li><li><strong>Manage customer orders</strong> quickly and accurately, especially during peak periods.</li><li><strong>Assist with opening and closing duties</strong> —\n     preparing ingredients, turning on/off machines, counting stock, closing\n     reports, other forms of cleaning and maintenance  </li><li>Other forms of<strong> basic customer service</strong>, including addressing complaints or special requests.\n     </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Proven experience as a baker, pastry chef and/or cafe settings, preferably with mini cakes and\n     pastries.</li><li>Able to stand for long hours and handle fast-paced environments.</li><li>Able to work <strong>weekends, evenings, shifts and Public Holidays (PH)</strong> as needed.</li><li>Salary to scale up based on skills and experience</li></ul>",
